---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="From SOP to Web App: Resources & Prompts | PipeHQ"
  description="The exact prompts used in the 'From SOP to Web App' presentation at the Christchurch AI Meetup. Copy these prompts to turn your manual processes into internal web apps using Claude and Manus."
  canonicalUrl="/chchai"
>
  <Header slot="header" />

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-neutral-900 pt-16 pb-14 md:pt-24 md:pb-20">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-primary bg-blue-950 rounded-full mb-5 tracking-wide uppercase">
        Christchurch AI Meetup
      </span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white leading-tight">
        From SOP to Web App
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-3 text-xl font-medium text-blue-300">Resources &amp; Prompts</p>
      <p class="mt-6 text-base md:text-lg text-neutral-400 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Thanks for coming along tonight. Below are the exact prompts I used in the presentation
        — ready to copy, paste, and adapt to your own processes. You don't need to be a developer.
        You just need a process worth automating.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Divider -->
  <div class="h-1 bg-gradient-to-r from-primary via-blue-400 to-accent"></div>

  <!-- Main content -->
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-14 md:py-20 space-y-16">

    <!-- ── Section 1: The Prompt Workflow ── -->
    <section>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">🔁</span>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary uppercase tracking-widest">Section 1</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">
        The Claude-to-Manus Prompt Workflow
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-10">
        Run these four prompts in order. Start each session with your SOP pasted in — a Word doc, a Google Doc export,
        or even rough bullet points all work fine.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-8">

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 bg-neutral-50 px-5 py-4 border-b border-neutral-200">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-white text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center">1</span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Step 1</p>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900">The Brain Dump</h3>
            </div>
            <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-medium text-neutral-400 bg-neutral-200 px-2 py-1 rounded">Paste into Claude with your SOP</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <pre class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap font-mono overflow-x-auto"><code>I want to turn this process into an internal web app. For now, just read this and summarize the core workflow back to me so I know you understand it. Do not write any code or propose features yet.</code></pre>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">
              <strong>Why:</strong> Forces the AI to demonstrate comprehension before it starts building.
              Catch misunderstandings early, not after 200 lines of code.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 bg-neutral-50 px-5 py-4 border-b border-neutral-200">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-white text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center">2</span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Step 2</p>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900">The Product Manager</h3>
            </div>
            <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-medium text-neutral-400 bg-neutral-200 px-2 py-1 rounded">In Claude</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <pre class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap font-mono overflow-x-auto"><code>Act as a Product Manager. Based on the SOP I just provided, propose a feature list for an MVP web app. Focus specifically on defining the User Roles, the Inputs required, and the desired Outputs.</code></pre>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">
              <strong>Why:</strong> Structures your thinking around people, data, and outcomes — the three things that make or break an MVP.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 bg-neutral-50 px-5 py-4 border-b border-neutral-200">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-primary text-white text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center">3</span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Step 3</p>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900">The Spec Sheet</h3>
            </div>
            <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-medium text-neutral-400 bg-neutral-200 px-2 py-1 rounded">In Claude</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <pre class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap font-mono overflow-x-auto"><code>Write a comprehensive Product Requirements Document (PRD) that I can paste into an AI app builder. It must explicitly define the database tables, the user roles, and the error states (the unhappy path).</code></pre>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">
              <strong>Why:</strong> This PRD is the blueprint you hand to Manus. The more specific it is, the better the output.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 4 -->
        <div class="rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 overflow-hidden border-accent/30 ring-1 ring-accent/20">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-4 bg-orange-50 px-5 py-4 border-b border-accent/20">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-accent text-white text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center">4</span>
            <div>
              <p class="text-xs font-semibold text-orange-500 uppercase tracking-wider">Step 4</p>
              <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-neutral-900">The Execution</h3>
            </div>
            <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-medium text-orange-600 bg-orange-100 px-2 py-1 rounded">Paste the PRD into Manus</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5">
            <pre class="bg-neutral-900 text-green-300 rounded-lg p-4 text-sm leading-relaxed whitespace-pre-wrap font-mono overflow-x-auto"><code>I want to build a web app based on this PRD. Take ownership of this project. Present a development plan for my review before you start coding.</code></pre>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-neutral-500">
              <strong>Why:</strong> "Take ownership" signals that Manus should drive — but asking for a plan first
              means you stay in control before a single line of code is written.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <hr class="border-neutral-200" />

    <!-- ── Section 2: Pro Tips ── -->
    <section>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">💡</span>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary uppercase tracking-widest">Section 2</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">
        Pro Tips for Better Apps
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-8">
        These three habits separate apps that actually work from ones that look good in the demo and fall apart on day two.
      </p>

      <ul class="space-y-5">
        <li class="flex gap-4 p-5 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Define Data DNA First</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Prompt for database tables, not just UI. If you don't tell the AI what data to store and how it relates, it'll invent a structure that breaks when you scale.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="flex gap-4 p-5 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Specify the Unhappy Path</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Tell the AI what should happen when things go wrong. For example: <em>"If a user forgets to upload a document, show a red error message and disable the submit button."</em> AI builders default to the happy path — you need to explicitly define the edges.</p>
          </div>
        </li>

        <li class="flex gap-4 p-5 bg-blue-50 rounded-xl border border-blue-100">
          <span class="flex-shrink-0 mt-0.5 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-primary flex items-center justify-center">
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-white" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Request an Admin Dashboard</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mt-1">Always ask for an admin view. It forces the AI to build real database reads and writes — not just a pretty form that saves to nowhere. If the admin view works, your data model works.</p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <!-- Divider -->
    <hr class="border-neutral-200" />

    <!-- ── Section 3: Ideas to Build ── -->
    <section>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-2">
        <span class="text-2xl">🚀</span>
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-primary uppercase tracking-widest">Section 3</p>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-3">
        Ideas to Build Today
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-8">
        You don't need a SaaS idea. Internal tools that save your team 2–3 hours a week are worth building.
        Here are five starting points for non-developers.
      </p>

      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 hover:border-primary/40 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🧑‍💼</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Client Onboarding Portal</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Collects client info, uploads documents, and automatically generates a task checklist for your team. No more chasing emails.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 hover:border-primary/40 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">📈</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Social Media Growth Tracker</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">A custom dashboard to log follower counts, engagement, and content performance — tailored to the metrics that actually matter to you.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 hover:border-primary/40 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🎓</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Employee Training &amp; Quiz App</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Internal training modules with pass/fail quizzes. Track who's completed what, and flag gaps before they become problems.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 hover:border-primary/40 hover:shadow-sm transition-all">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">🎯</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Lead Qualification Scoring Tool</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Answer a few questions about a lead and get a score out of 100. Helps your sales team prioritise without gut-feel guessing.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl border border-neutral-200 hover:border-primary/40 hover:shadow-sm transition-all sm:col-span-2">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-3">📦</div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-1">Inventory &amp; Asset Checkout System</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500">Log what equipment or assets you have, who's checked them out, and when they're due back. Simple, searchable, and actually used.</p>
        </div>

      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <!-- ── Section 4: CTA ── -->
  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-neutral-900 via-blue-950 to-neutral-900 py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 text-center">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Ready to build?</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-5 leading-tight">
        Your first app is one PRD away.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-neutral-400 text-base md:text-lg mb-8 leading-relaxed">
        Manus is an agentic AI platform that turns your PRD into a working web app. Use the invitation
        link below to get access and start building your first internal tool today.
      </p>
      <a
        href="https://manus.im/invitation/EBUGZUSJVWNZ6GJ?utm_source=invitation&utm_medium=social&utm_campaign=copy_link"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-7 py-4 text-base font-semibold text-white bg-accent hover:bg-accent-dark rounded-xl transition-colors shadow-lg shadow-orange-900/30"
      >
        Claim Your Manus Invitation &amp; Start Building
        <svg class="w-5 h-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M10 6H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v10a2 2 0 002 2h10a2 2 0 002-2v-4M14 4h6m0 0v6m0-6L10 14" />
        </svg>
      </a>
      <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm mt-4">
        Used in the presentation. No affiliation — just a tool that works.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer slot="footer" />
</BaseLayout>
